<p>A Federal High Court in Abuja convicted Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) leader Nnamdi Kanu on seven terrorism-related counts and sentenced him to life imprisonment, concluding a decade-long case that has inflamed tensions in Nigeria’s southeast [rt.com#1][allafrica.com#2][straitstimes.com#1]. The ruling can be appealed [semafor.com#1]. Kanu’s legal saga began with his 2015 arrest and included his 2021 return to Nigeria [allafrica.com#1][rt.com#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Kanu was convicted on all seven terrorism charges at the Federal High Court in Abuja and received a life sentence [rt.com#1][allafrica.com#2][straitstimes.com#1]</li><li>The court found he used IPOB and broadcasts to incite attacks and that he ordered illegal Monday “sit-at-home” shutdowns in the southeast [rt.com#1][semafor.com#1]</li><li>Prosecutors sought the death penalty, but the judge imposed life imprisonment instead, saying capital punishment is now “frowned upon” [rt.com#1]</li><li>The ruling can be appealed [semafor.com#1]</li><li>Timeline highlights: 2015 arrest; 2017 bail and flight; 2017 IPOB designated a terrorist group; 2021 seizure in Kenya and return; Nov. 2025 conviction and life sentence [allafrica.com#1][rt.com#1][semafor.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][allafrica.com#2]</li></ul><blockquote>capital punishment is now &quot;frowned upon&quot; - Justice James Omotosho</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Federal High Court (Justice James Omotosho): The court convicted Kanu on seven terrorism counts and sentenced him to life imprisonment; it ruled he used IPOB and Radio Biafra broadcasts to incite attacks and noted illegal Monday “sit-at-home” orders [rt.com#1][semafor.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/africa/628103-nigeria-hands-biafra-separatist-leader-life-sentence/'>RT.com</a>)</li><li>Nnamdi Kanu/IPOB: Kanu argued the proceedings were unlawful and that the court lacked jurisdiction; he dismissed his legal team and chose to represent himself [rt.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/africa/628103-nigeria-hands-biafra-separatist-leader-life-sentence/'>RT.com</a>)</li><li>Nigerian government: The government designated IPOB a terrorist organization in 2017, citing alleged acts of violence [semafor.com#1][rt.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.semafor.com/article/11/21/2025/nigeria-jails-biafra-separatist-leader-nnamdi-kanu-for-life'>Semafor</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202511210135.html'>Nigeria: Timeline - Inside Nnamdi Kanu&#x27;s Journey From Biafra Activism to Conviction for Terrorism</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://www.semafor.com/article/11/21/2025/nigeria-jails-biafra-separatist-leader-nnamdi-kanu-for-life'>Nigeria jails Biafra separatist leader Nnamdi Kanu for life</a> - semafor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/africa/628103-nigeria-hands-biafra-separatist-leader-life-sentence/'>Nigeria jails separatist leader for life over terrorism (VIDEO)</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/nigerian-court-jails-separatist-leader-kanu-for-life-over-terrorism'>Nigerian court jails separatist leader Kanu for life over terrorism</a> - straitstimes.com</li></ul>